# Development Workflow Rule

## Daily SOP (Scheme A)
1. Edit only repository files.
2. Validate locally by running installer to update `~/bin`.
3. Run verification commands.
4. Commit repository changes.

## Verification commands
- `command -v switch-env`
- `switch-env doctor`
- `switch-env status`

## Packaging command
- `AUTO_YES=1 ./install-switch-env.sh --build switch-env-installer.sh`

## Installation simulation
- `AUTO_YES=1 bash ./install-switch-env.sh`

## Consistency rule
- Never manually keep repository and `~/bin` in sync by copy/overwrite.
- Repository changes must flow into `~/bin` through installer behavior.
